race.comment: ZENTORNO (6) resumes for his second campaign having been thereabouts in two runs last time in, especially on debut at Pakenham in a stronger race when fifth, beaten three lengths. Tipping he'll be improved this time around and can get off the mark. CYNANE (7) has only managed one placing from six starts to date but finds a winnable race here, not beaten far at her past two starts at Mt Gambier and Bordertown. Gets Meech on which helps. SUPIDO'S LITTLEONE (4) is a 23 start maiden but put in a solid effort at Swan Hill when last seen. A repeat of that has her in the mix. BOULDEROO (5) struggled on debut at Echuca but has less convictions than most of these and could improve. SARAYA (3) was better last start although this isn't easier.
